Key Match Events: Giannis Antetokounmpo finished with 30 points and 12 rebounds as the Milwaukee Bucks rallied from a 19-point deficit and beat the Indiana Pacers 120-112
Post-Match Reflections: Giannis Antetokounmpo stepped up in the second half after the Bucks fell behind 83-64 in the third quarter
Miscellaneous Highlights: Bennedict Mathurin led the Pacers with 25 points
Others: Brook Lopez scored 16 points and Bobby Portis Jr. had 14 points and 15 rebounds for the Bucks
Pascal Siakam had 20 points for the Pacers
